Package com.shouldis.bitset.parallel

Class FunctionBiterator

java.lang.Object
com.shouldis.bitset.parallel.Biterator
com.shouldis.bitset.parallel.FunctionBiterator
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.Spliterator<java.lang.Integer>, java.util.Spliterator.OfInt, java.util.Spliterator.OfPrimitive<java.lang.Integer,​java.util.function.IntConsumer,​java.util.Spliterator.OfInt>
Direct Known Subclasses:
FunctionBiterator.And, FunctionBiterator.Or, FunctionBiterator.XOr
public abstract class FunctionBiterator
extends Biterator
Implementation of Biterator that creates a stream of indices that represents which bits will be live after performing a bitwiseFunction(long, long) between the words of 2 BitSets at the same word index. The three main operations: FunctionBiterator.And, FunctionBiterator.Or, and FunctionBiterator.XOr are provided by this class.
Author:
Aaron Shouldis

  • Constructor Details

    • FunctionBiterator

      protected FunctionBiterator​(BitSet set1, BitSet set2, int position, int end)
      Creates a FunctionBiterator with the specified starting and ending position. This FunctionBiterator will perform bitwise operations on the words of the specified BitSets.
      Parameters:
      set1 - the first BitSet, which will be operated on against set2.
      set2 - the second BitSet, which will be operated on against set1.
      position - (inclusive) the first index to include.
      end - (exclusive) index after the last index to include.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if position is greater than or equal to end, or the sizes of set1 and set2 differ.
      java.lang.NullPointerException - if set1 or set2 are null.

      private final int next​(int index)
      Calculates the index of the next live bit after the specified index, including that index. All bits indices, until Biterator.end will be checked. If no live bits are found, Biterator.end is returned.
      Parameters:
      index - (inclusive) the first index to check.
      Returns:
      the index of the next live bit, or Biterator.end if none were found.
